Its understood a mini bus taxi was transporting disabled children to a special needs school earlier today. JOHANNESBURG - One child has been killed and 24 others injured after a mini bus taxi collided with a bakkie on the R25 in Bronkhorstspruit. Its understood the mini bus was transporting disabled children to a special needs school earlier today when the crash happened. The driver of the bakkie was declared dead on the scene. Netcare 911's Athlenda Mathesays the injured are receiving medical attention. Two of the disabled children are in a critical condition, the rest sustained minor to moderate injuries and the Netcare helicopter airlifted one of the children to a hospital in Johannesburg for further medical care.